name: Cafe Ashwini

reviews.review_text: New branch of Cafe Ashwini. Pure veg unlike previous branch. More spacious. A/C section available. Takeaway available. Quantity not consistent. (Photos attached). I had to order 2 qty for 1. Breakfast is tasty. Newer items like idli/dosa etc. In menu. But availability a serious issue. Service is slow esp. In AC section. Veg thali is quiet wholesome. One of the best. Evening hard to get anything hot to eat. Wadas, samosas, Mirchies made in the morning served cold. The dosa also served is cold. Would recommend for visiting it for breakfast and veg lunch. Open on sundays (morning half).

Lovely place for quick breakfast or Chinese Indian food. Try their Goan breakfast, you will never regret. Loved everything on the menu. Affordable and quick. They have the main outlet at St. Inez which is small yet dishes out best and yummy food. This is a new one, good enough place to sit and enjoy

Ashwini is one place I've loved a lot ever since I was in my 20s and they do the best mixed bhaji which is called the sangam bhaji and the best way to eat it is with Unde which is the brother of the pao.Also their samosa with the coconut chutney and tomato ketchup is really yummy and not forgetting their fluffy buns.

description:
**Welcome to Cafe Ashwini: A Culinary Haven in Caranzalem**

Nestled in the vibrant locale of Caranzalem, Cafe Ashwini delights its patrons with a stellar rating of 4.3 based on over 1,300 reviews. This pure vegetarian eatery is garnering attention for its diverse offerings, including unforgettable breakfasts, hearty bhaji, and tantalizing mushroom samosas. Frequent mentions of affordability and quick service highlight its charm as a favored spot for both locals and visitors alike.

**Ambiance & Design**

Upon stepping into Cafe Ashwini, guests are greeted by a spacious interior that's a step up from its previous branch, featuring air conditioning for those warm, tropical days. Bright lighting enhances the welcoming atmosphere, creating a comfortable environment perfect for casual dining. The recent photos available show a tastefully decorated space, complete with minimalistic yet functional furniture that allows for easy movement, and a pleasant arrangement conducive to both small gatherings and quick meals.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

The menu at Cafe Ashwini offers a delightful range of vegetarian options designed to cater to diverse palates. Signature dishes include their renowned mixed bhaji, affectionately known as sangam bhaji, which, as one enthusiastic reviewer noted, is best enjoyed with freshly baked unde—which serves as a delightful cousin to the traditional pao. The breakfast selection is a standout, with items like idli and dosa making an appearance, though reviews hint at inconsistency in availability. Diners will appreciate the wholesomeness of their veg thali, while the warmth and fluffiness of their buns and the allure of mushroom samosas truly elevate the experience.

**Customer Experience & Service**

Customer feedback reflects a generally positive experience, though some diners have noted that service can be slow at times, particularly in the air-conditioned section. Reservations or walk-ins are welcome, with a particular recommendation to visit for breakfast or during the lunch hours to ensure the freshest food on offer. Guests have pointed out that early or nach evening visits might lead to less desirable options, such as cold wadas and samosas.

**Popularity & Reviews**

Cafe Ashwini has quickly become a popular breakfast haunt, particularly lauded for its lovely Goan breakfast offerings. Patrons frequently praise the affordability combined with the quality of food, making it an ideal choice for quick meals or leisurely brunches. The social media buzz around the establishment reflects its growing reputation, with many choosing to share their experiences—both for the food and the inviting atmosphere.

**Utilizing Visual Content**

The provided images from happy diners perfectly illustrate the vibrant colors and appetizing presentation of the dishes served at Cafe Ashwini. One can see the appealing arrangement of the food, making it even more tempting. Visually, the restaurant succeeds in creating an inviting space that feels warm and casual, befitting its image as a local favorite.

In summary, Cafe Ashwini in Caranzalem stands out not just for its culinary offerings, but for its friendly atmosphere and engaging dining experience. With a recommended visit for breakfast, cafe-goers are sure to find something that appeals to both their taste buds and their wallets.
